 const binaryRepresentation = Array.from(str, char => char.charCodeAt(0).toString(2)); console.log(binaryRepresentation); // [\\"1001000\\", \\"1100101\\", \\"1101100\\", \\"1101100\\", \\"1101111\\"] \`\`\` 2. Perform a bitwise operation: Once you have the binary representation of the string, you can perform bitwise operations like OR (\`|\`), AND (\`&\`), XOR (\`^\`), left shift (\`<<\`), right shift (\`>>\`), etc. on them. Remember to convert the binary strings back to decimal using \`parseInt()\` if needed. Here's an example of performing a bitwise OR on two binary strings: \`\`\`javascript const binary1 = \\"1001000\\"; const binary2 = \\"1100101\\"; const result = parseInt(binary1, 2) | parseInt(binary2, 2); console.log(result.toString(2)); // \\"1101101\\" \`\`\` Note: Bitwise operations are typically applied on numbers rather than strings. By converting strings to binary representation, you can perform these operations indirectly on the string's underlying binary data. However, bitwise operations may not yield meaningful results in all scenarios when applied directly on strings."},{"prompt":"continue the titles 1 One More For The Road Lyrics 2 Nobody Likes A Tough Guy Lyrics 3 You Just Know What To Do Lyrics 4 I Can Make Things Better If You Let Me Lyrics 5 Pick A Date And Stick With It Lyrics 6 Give It The Old College Try Lyrics 7 There Was Nothing More We Could Do Lyrics 8 I Knew You Would Come Back Lyrics 9 All The Things You Should Get Over Lyrics 10 If I Had A Boat Lyrics","completion":"The titles you've listed appear to be part of a sequence of song titles or poetry lines, though since they are not well-known titles from a popular and existing artist, or part of the public domain, it's not possible to continue them with certain accuracy. However, I can create fictional continuations inspired by the themes and storytelling often found in music and poetry. Here is a fictional list of continuations based on the titles you provided: 11. Riding Waves Of Des